WEBVTT

00:04.337 --> 00:06.703
[Theme music]

00:08.000 --> 00:14.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:39.505 --> 00:41.336
Two and an eighth.

00:42.174 --> 00:44.642
And two and a sixteenth.

00:45.344 --> 00:47.505
Better let some air out of my left tires.

00:47.579 --> 00:50.776
BILL: Hey, getting your lawn ready
for Cinco de Mayo?

00:51.083 --> 00:54.416
Bill, my lawn is in a constant state
of readiness.

00:54.486 --> 00:57.284
The block party is just an opportunity
to trot her out...

00:57.356 --> 00:58.823
and show what she can do.

00:59.158 --> 01:02.457
<i>KAHN: Since you let your lawn go to hell,
okay if Doggie make on it?</i>

01:02.594 --> 01:04.994
If you've got something to say, say it.

01:05.063 --> 01:07.930
It's not my place to point out
low density patches here...

01:08.066 --> 01:10.967
over there, and behind other side of house.

01:11.336 --> 01:14.169
<i>Sucky lawn bring down
value of my property.</i>

01:14.506 --> 01:16.497
DALE: Now, you listen here, Kahn...

01:16.575 --> 01:19.669
if anyone's bringing down
the value of this neighborhood...

01:19.878 --> 01:21.038
it's me.

01:21.146 --> 01:24.172
My lawn's nothing
but ragweed and auto parts.

01:24.249 --> 01:26.979
I should be ashamed
to live next to Hank Hill.

01:27.052 --> 01:29.179
He's got the best lawn in Arlen.

01:29.254 --> 01:31.552
Best lawn after mine!

01:31.890 --> 01:33.653
[Kahn laughing]

01:35.627 --> 01:36.958
BILL: Don't worry, Hank.

01:37.029 --> 01:40.089
We might be able to tell
Kahn's lawn is better than yours.

01:40.165 --> 01:43.191
But all those people
at the block party, they won't.

01:43.268 --> 01:44.895
They'll be drunk.

01:48.841 --> 01:52.038
Damn, I've poured
my whole life into this lawn.

01:52.211 --> 01:54.008
My heart, my soul.

01:54.880 --> 01:58.407
The tender feelings
I've held back from my family.

01:59.084 --> 02:02.212
Now, Hank, you don't
want to win that way.

02:02.521 --> 02:06.548
Why don't you just switch those back,
and go in and hug your wife?

02:09.328 --> 02:12.695
Bethany, it does not matter
if your avocados are hard.

02:13.031 --> 02:14.498
Life is hard.

02:14.700 --> 02:17.134
You cannot make authentic guacamole...

02:17.202 --> 02:19.727
out of lima beans and Ritz crackers.

02:20.539 --> 02:22.734
<i>Oh, these people! Gringos!</i>

02:22.975 --> 02:26.536
I am just glad you're in charge
of the block party this year, Aunt Peggy.

02:27.112 --> 02:29.876
Last year, it was all Tex and no Mex.

02:30.249 --> 02:34.743
HANK: I don't know why everyone's
so gaga over Kahn's lawn all of a sudden.

02:34.920 --> 02:37.912
For God's sakes,
the man mows with the grain.

02:38.090 --> 02:39.114
He's the devil.

02:39.191 --> 02:41.557
Anyway, Hank,
would you please tell Boomhauer...

02:41.627 --> 02:43.527
<i>Swiss cheese is not Mexican.</i>

02:43.595 --> 02:45.119
<i>It is American.</i>

02:45.264 --> 02:48.165
I want him to bring some Monterey Jack.

02:48.233 --> 02:49.791
I'm the block captain.

02:49.868 --> 02:53.235
I should have the best lawn
for Cinco de Mayo.

02:53.305 --> 02:55.170
<i>But look at her. Something's wrong.</i>

02:55.240 --> 02:58.038
<i>She's like a pretty girl with short hair.</i>

02:59.645 --> 03:02.375
Hank, what do you say
to another lawn spraying...

03:02.447 --> 03:04.312
from your favorite exterminator?

03:04.383 --> 03:06.351
Well, I don't know.

03:06.418 --> 03:10.411
I guess those twice-a-week sprayings
have been doing the job, Dale.

03:10.489 --> 03:12.354
I lost another client.

03:12.991 --> 03:15.425
Thinks I use too much chemicals.

03:15.894 --> 03:19.295
<i>I say Sara Lee uses more chemicals
than I do.</i>

03:19.531 --> 03:23.399
Come on, I need to make up the income.
I'll do it for free.

03:24.202 --> 03:26.534
Well, okay.

03:26.605 --> 03:29.597
Wingo, man! I'll get my stuff.

03:30.075 --> 03:32.270
Maybe that's what's wrong
with your lawn.

03:32.344 --> 03:34.335
Dale's spraying too much poison on it?

03:34.413 --> 03:37.871
What? No. He's always sprayed my lawn.

03:38.183 --> 03:42.279
If I can give some business to my friend
and keep my lawn bug-free...

03:42.354 --> 03:44.015
it's worth $2 a week.

03:44.089 --> 03:47.456
Good for you for choosing your friend
over your lawn.

03:49.461 --> 03:50.519
DALE: All right!

03:50.596 --> 03:54.032
Turn your cuffs down, boys.
And make sure you're zipped.

03:54.099 --> 03:55.589
You know what, Dale?

03:55.667 --> 03:58.932
I thought it over,
and I think I'll take a rain check.

03:59.004 --> 04:01.837
But I was gonna spray for fire ants today.

04:01.907 --> 04:04.171
All the same, I'll give it a pass.

04:04.242 --> 04:08.110
DALE: I wouldn't advise that.
You risk getting a queen.

04:08.513 --> 04:09.912
Look at her!

04:10.616 --> 04:13.983
<i>She can lay a million eggs
in a 24-hour period.</i>

04:14.219 --> 04:18.212
BILL: Wow! That's more than
a human woman does in a lifetime.

04:18.290 --> 04:22.522
These fire ants are well-organized,
highly-trained insects.

04:22.594 --> 04:25.927
<i>They'll swarm all over you
and sting you all at once...</i>

04:25.998 --> 04:28.660
<i>without warning, on a single command.</i>

04:29.001 --> 04:31.492
It's how they killed L. Ron Hubbard.

04:32.070 --> 04:35.665
Dale, fire ants don't sting you all at once.

04:35.941 --> 04:38.933
Half of them bite,
the other half are on defense.

04:39.011 --> 04:40.478
That's not true.

04:40.545 --> 04:43.844
I don't know, man. Hank's the man.
He knows. Dang old Hank's the man.

04:43.915 --> 04:46.076
What are you guys listening to Hank for?

04:46.151 --> 04:51.589
I have dedicated my professional career
to the study and control of arthropods.

04:51.957 --> 04:56.451
I've personally taste-tested
each and every household insecticide.

04:56.561 --> 04:58.290
<i>I have read a book.</i>

04:58.463 --> 05:00.795
Now, who do you believe, me or Hank?

05:00.866 --> 05:02.834
Hank is more believable.

05:02.968 --> 05:04.936
<i>Fine. Side with him.</i>

05:05.137 --> 05:09.836
Just to show you what a big man I am,
I'll still spray your lawn.

05:10.676 --> 05:13.839
Dale, I don't want you
to spray my lawn anymore.

05:13.912 --> 05:15.812
Not now, not ever.

05:16.314 --> 05:19.181
I see what's going on here.

05:19.251 --> 05:21.446
You got another exterminator.

05:21.687 --> 05:25.384
Is he licensed? Is he bonded? Is that it?

05:25.457 --> 05:28.187
Did you want someone
who's licensed and bonded?

05:28.260 --> 05:31.718
Dale, let's not make this any harder
than it has to be.

05:31.797 --> 05:33.025
It's over.

05:33.098 --> 05:36.067
But I'm your exterminator.

05:36.268 --> 05:38.031
You were my exterminator.

05:38.270 --> 05:40.170
Now we're just friends.

05:43.375 --> 05:45.570
Don't do this to me in front of everybody.

05:45.644 --> 05:48.841
Let me just spray a little
to keep up appearances.

05:48.914 --> 05:49.938
No.

05:52.484 --> 05:54.042
[Makes spraying noises]

05:57.589 --> 05:58.613
[Clears throat]

05:58.690 --> 06:00.089
All done, Hank.

06:00.158 --> 06:03.093
Just keep the dog in the house for an hour.

06:04.196 --> 06:08.724
HANK: I did what had to be done.
I got rid of an anti-lawn element.

06:09.501 --> 06:12.368
<i>Sure, he's a friend.
But I have lots of friends.</i>

06:13.605 --> 06:15.539
<i>I only have the one lawn.</i>

06:21.780 --> 06:24.772
What do you think?
Does this say "Hank Hill"?

06:24.916 --> 06:27.817
I thought we just came
for seed and fertilizer.

06:27.886 --> 06:30.320
Why are men so attracted to hoes?

06:31.189 --> 06:33.487
HANK: Peggy, look!

06:33.558 --> 06:35.651
<i>It's Raleigh St. Augustine!</i>

06:35.994 --> 06:38.588
To hell with fertilizer and seed.
I want this!

06:38.663 --> 06:41.757
It's $1.25 a square foot.

06:41.833 --> 06:43.960
<i>So what? It's worth it.</i>

06:44.269 --> 06:47.636
Look, some people hoist a flag
to show they love our country.

06:47.706 --> 06:49.731
My lawn is my flag.

06:50.242 --> 06:51.903
It tells the world:

06:51.977 --> 06:56.107
"Here lives a competent,
trustworthy salesman of propane...

06:56.181 --> 06:58.046
"and propane accessories."

06:58.116 --> 07:01.882
A man who can't keep up a lawn
is either inept or stupid.

07:02.053 --> 07:04.851
Without my lawn, I am Bill.

07:05.090 --> 07:07.524
Do you want to be married to Bill?

07:07.626 --> 07:08.615
<i>[Shudders]</i>

07:15.901 --> 07:20.031
Well, mister, you have just installed
the finest lawn on the block.

07:20.105 --> 07:23.905
HANK: Peggy, I didn't do it for me.
I did it for Arlen.

07:25.043 --> 07:27.179
It looks so nice. Can I touch it?

07:27.312 --> 07:30.543
<i>Sure, it's a lawn. It's meant to be enjoyed.</i>

07:31.449 --> 07:33.041
[Childish giggling]

07:34.085 --> 07:37.612
It feels so good against my skin.

07:38.023 --> 07:39.650
[Laughing]

07:45.830 --> 07:47.627
Okay, that's enough.

07:51.236 --> 07:54.797
DALE: Hey, Hank,
congrats on the lawn, friend.

07:56.007 --> 07:57.497
I'm glad you came.

07:57.576 --> 07:59.567
- May I?
- Just a little.

08:00.078 --> 08:03.514
DALE: Oh, yeah. That's nice.

08:03.982 --> 08:06.473
Feels like a shag carpet with dirt.

08:06.885 --> 08:09.012
Feels like home.

08:09.087 --> 08:11.078
KAHN: Hey! Get off my property!

08:11.556 --> 08:12.580
[Giggling]

08:12.657 --> 08:15.285
Luanne! For God's sakes!

08:15.727 --> 08:17.922
<i>[Sinister instrumental music]</i>

08:20.298 --> 08:21.925
[Dale chuckling]

08:23.335 --> 08:24.495
Ouch!

08:35.513 --> 08:37.309
<i>[Sighs happily]</i>

08:37.749 --> 08:40.240
Boy, it does feel good against the skin.

08:40.318 --> 08:43.719
<i>KAHN: Hank Hill, somebody steal
my TV Guide out of mailbox!</i>

08:44.022 --> 08:47.719
First, I think it Bill.
But then I think, can Bill read?

08:47.792 --> 08:50.852
Hey, Kahn.
Just letting my feet air out here.

08:50.962 --> 08:54.056
KAHN: Hillbilly barefoot. Big surprise!

08:54.299 --> 08:57.166
Yep, just walking around on my lush...

08:57.435 --> 08:59.369
super-plush, new lawn.

08:59.437 --> 09:02.565
<i>I notice. Raleigh St. Augustine.
Very expensive.</i>

09:02.707 --> 09:05.972
I think it was worth it
for the best lawn in Arlen.

09:06.044 --> 09:07.909
Yes, all right. You win. Best lawn.

09:07.979 --> 09:10.140
Tomorrow, maybe we compare salaries.

09:10.215 --> 09:13.981
<i>Kahn Jr., get fertilizer!
Minh, get my tax return!</i>

09:17.122 --> 09:19.556
Don't want to get a hose imprint.

09:20.492 --> 09:21.516
Ow!

09:21.593 --> 09:23.026
What the...

09:23.261 --> 09:24.626
A fire ant?

09:25.864 --> 09:26.888
[Moaning]

09:26.965 --> 09:30.628
Oh, God, no! An ant hill on my new lawn!

09:30.702 --> 09:32.795
<i>So that's what that is.</i>

09:33.104 --> 09:35.197
How did I get fire ants?

09:35.307 --> 09:37.639
DALE: I'm only
a professional exterminator.

09:37.709 --> 09:41.475
<i>I don't know how you get them.
I only know how you get rid of them.</i>

09:41.579 --> 09:43.171
Got to go.

09:44.949 --> 09:46.507
It's called Eco-Kill, Hank.

09:46.584 --> 09:49.314
The government would not
let them use the word "eco"...

09:49.387 --> 09:51.082
unless it was ecologically safe.

09:52.457 --> 09:54.448
I don't know, Peggy. It seems to me...

09:54.526 --> 09:56.721
it's gonna take more than a bag of flies...

09:56.795 --> 09:59.457
to scare off these red devil bastards.

09:59.597 --> 10:02.691
No. They do more than scare them.

10:02.901 --> 10:06.894
<i>"The Ford fly injects its egg
into the fire ant's head.</i>

10:07.305 --> 10:11.435
<i>"The egg hatches into a maggot,
which eats away at the ant's brain...</i>

10:11.509 --> 10:14.273
"until the head falls off.
Repeat as necessary."

10:14.346 --> 10:15.677
I like it.

10:15.747 --> 10:18.648
This is exactly
what those environmentalists...

10:18.717 --> 10:20.651
should be spending their time on.

10:20.719 --> 10:22.744
<i>Finding ways to use nature...</i>

10:22.821 --> 10:24.516
<i>against other forms of nature...</i>

10:24.589 --> 10:26.784
that are inconvenient to man.

10:27.192 --> 10:29.717
Wow, look how busy this ant is.

10:29.994 --> 10:32.292
<i>It's got so many places to go...</i>

10:32.364 --> 10:34.264
and so many things to do.

10:34.899 --> 10:35.991
Oops.

10:37.502 --> 10:40.801
<i>JOSEPH: Your parents got Eco-Kill. Cool!</i>

10:41.306 --> 10:43.900
We can collect the empty ant heads
when they're done.

10:43.975 --> 10:46.102
What a terrible way to die.

10:46.478 --> 10:47.467
Oops.

10:47.579 --> 10:50.673
Come on! If we save them,
we can play with them.

11:03.828 --> 11:06.319
BOBBY: Hey, look at that
chubby white one.

11:06.531 --> 11:09.694
<i>He reminds me of me,
before my growth spurt.</i>

11:09.768 --> 11:11.793
That's the queen, stupid.

11:11.870 --> 11:14.270
It looks just like
the one on my dad's truck.

11:14.339 --> 11:17.399
- You mean Dale Gribble's truck?
- Yeah, my dad!

11:17.909 --> 11:19.399
The queen is cool.

11:19.477 --> 11:23.413
<i>She lets out smells that make
the other ants do whatever she wants.</i>

11:24.115 --> 11:25.173
Wow!

11:29.387 --> 11:30.718
DALE: Well, well, well.

11:30.789 --> 11:33.815
Looks like those fire ants
played you like the damn fiddle.

11:33.892 --> 11:36.087
Yeah? Well, the opry ain't over yet.

11:36.161 --> 11:39.619
Okay, ants, put your heads
between your six legs...

11:39.697 --> 11:41.790
and kiss your butt goodbye.

11:50.542 --> 11:53.602
"Celebration of local graffiti artists"?

11:53.878 --> 11:55.345
I'll give you a headline.

11:55.413 --> 11:58.746
"Local man cancels
newspaper subscription."

12:00.351 --> 12:01.375
[Kahn laughing]

12:01.453 --> 12:04.889
Hey, Hank! You got a permit
for all that construction?

12:06.391 --> 12:08.018
You've got ants.

12:08.193 --> 12:10.058
[Rock music playing on radio]

12:11.696 --> 12:12.993
<i>[Sniffing]</i>

12:24.776 --> 12:26.835
Yes, my queen.

12:32.817 --> 12:35.251
<i>[Soft-rock music playing]</i>

12:36.988 --> 12:40.822
BILL: Peggy wants me to barbecue
20 pounds of Mexican sausage.

12:41.359 --> 12:44.294
I got half a tank of propane left.
You think that's enough?

12:44.362 --> 12:47.456
I figure I can top it off with some
lighter fluid or something.

12:47.532 --> 12:51.491
Bill, you don't want to be
mixing and matching your petrochemical.

12:51.870 --> 12:54.532
The Propane Association
recommends that you...

12:54.606 --> 12:57.097
It'll be fine, Bill. Burn is burn.

12:57.408 --> 12:59.933
"Burn is burn." I got to remember that.

13:00.011 --> 13:02.605
No, no! I'm telling you, that's dangerous.

13:02.881 --> 13:04.906
Propane is what I know best.

13:04.983 --> 13:06.746
It sure ain't lawns.

13:08.786 --> 13:11.254
BOOMHAUER: Yeah, man,
dang sure right about that.

13:12.156 --> 13:15.819
Hey, guys,
I've kind of got to talk to Dale alone.

13:19.664 --> 13:22.861
<i>I was just telling the guys
about Stonehenge.</i>

13:22.934 --> 13:26.893
It seems the Druids used it
as some kind of sophisticated celestial...

13:26.971 --> 13:29.269
Dale, I didn't come here to...

13:29.340 --> 13:32.503
Oh, no! For once, you will hear me out.

13:33.778 --> 13:35.040
...calendar.

13:35.747 --> 13:37.374
Now what can I do for you?

13:37.448 --> 13:41.384
You can save my lawn.
Those fire ants are out of control.

13:41.753 --> 13:44.278
You're the only one who can help me.

13:44.355 --> 13:45.686
That's right.

13:45.757 --> 13:49.215
I am. The question is, why should I?

13:49.527 --> 13:51.427
Well, I'll give you $2.

13:51.563 --> 13:52.552
[Laughs]

13:52.964 --> 13:54.397
$2?

13:55.567 --> 13:57.558
Because you're my friend.

13:58.570 --> 14:02.097
I'm Hank's friend! Tie a ribbon around me.

14:02.640 --> 14:05.438
Because I'm coming to you, man to man...

14:05.510 --> 14:09.970
offering a genuine apology
for choosing my lawn over our friendship.

14:11.449 --> 14:14.384
Jeez, Hank, I was
just holding out for $2.50.

14:14.953 --> 14:18.650
What's that? What are you spraying?
There won't be bleaching, will there?

14:18.723 --> 14:19.849
Hell, no.

14:21.559 --> 14:24.323
I'd put that mask back on if I were you.

14:24.495 --> 14:26.731
<i>You should've come to me sooner.</i>

14:26.864 --> 14:28.855
I got to pull out the big gun.

14:29.100 --> 14:31.796
<i>Dioxaphiliphide 6000...</i>

14:32.269 --> 14:33.896
with techroline.

14:33.971 --> 14:34.960
[Dale chuckling]

14:35.206 --> 14:38.403
<i>DJs: And don't forget
it is Quatro de Mayo!</i>

14:38.476 --> 14:40.239
<i>DJ 1: That's right, brother.
DJ 2: Right.</i>

14:44.448 --> 14:46.177
[Hank whimpering]

14:50.688 --> 14:52.212
[Moaning]

14:52.823 --> 14:56.691
<i>It's not fair. She was so young and green.</i>

14:57.762 --> 15:00.253
I never even got a chance to mow her.

15:00.598 --> 15:02.361
It'll be okay, Hank.

15:02.600 --> 15:05.626
You will grow a new lawn
by next year's Cinco de Mayo.

15:05.703 --> 15:08.365
I can't go through this again.

15:08.973 --> 15:13.034
- From now on, wood chips and gravel.
- Now, you do not mean that.

15:13.911 --> 15:17.210
Ashes to ashes, man.
It's that dang old ashes to ashes.

15:17.281 --> 15:20.045
DALE: I only used
as much poison as necessary...

15:20.117 --> 15:22.711
and not a 55-gallon drum more.

15:22.787 --> 15:24.118
Poor Hank.

15:24.688 --> 15:26.622
<i>- Serves him right.
- Damn straight...</i>

15:26.690 --> 15:28.123
Yeah, yeah, it does.

15:28.192 --> 15:31.093
You know, where I come from,
we got a thing called karma.

15:31.162 --> 15:34.859
You do something bad,
it come back and bite you in the ass!

15:34.999 --> 15:36.899
Big, white, stubborn ass!

15:37.301 --> 15:39.997
HANK: Guys, I can hear you.

15:40.538 --> 15:43.974
LUANNE: Aunt Peggy,
Buckley wants to bring his.38...

15:44.041 --> 15:45.770
to shoot off at the block party.

15:45.843 --> 15:48.812
But Uncle Hank said
nothing bigger than a.22.

15:48.879 --> 15:51.712
PEGGY: Well, now, he is
the block captain, Luanne.

15:53.484 --> 15:57.682
<i>PEGGY: Now, I coat the churros
with az√∫car, or sugar.</i>

16:00.491 --> 16:03.654
How very odd.
Now what the heck was that?

16:04.995 --> 16:07.896
BOBBY: Feed, my queen. Feed.

16:14.939 --> 16:16.839
[Mud gurgling]

16:20.144 --> 16:23.238
I just hope Hank doesn't blame Dale
for what happened.

16:23.314 --> 16:26.772
No, Nancy, he knows Dale
was only doing his job.

16:26.851 --> 16:28.978
He gave him a 50-cent raise.

16:29.353 --> 16:32.550
Oh, sugar! We're out of sugar, sug'.

16:32.623 --> 16:34.648
I think there's more in the basement.

16:34.725 --> 16:36.386
Oh, no, I'll go get it.

16:39.797 --> 16:42.357
<i>[Suspenseful instrumental music]</i>

16:47.438 --> 16:48.462
Dale?

17:04.588 --> 17:06.579
[Muffled breathing]

17:09.326 --> 17:11.521
- Oh, my goodness!
- Hey, Peggy.

17:11.595 --> 17:13.358
How could you do it?

17:13.763 --> 17:16.561
How could you plant fire ants on our lawn?

17:16.834 --> 17:19.098
I'm denying that. That's my position.

17:19.169 --> 17:22.569
Dale, you wrote it on this map!
"3:00 a.m., planted ants."

17:22.640 --> 17:25.268
If all you're going on is my confession,
forget it.

17:25.342 --> 17:27.002
I'm simply not credible.

17:27.077 --> 17:31.013
Well, then, what on God's green earth
are you doing with all these fire ants?

17:32.383 --> 17:33.680
DALE: They're silk worms.

17:33.784 --> 17:34.773
Uh-huh.

17:35.052 --> 17:38.078
DALE: If you keep your mouth shut,
I'll make you a business suit.

17:38.489 --> 17:39.478
<i>[Sniffing]</i>

17:39.657 --> 17:43.115
No, I cannot allow you to leave
the safety of the bowl.

17:43.460 --> 17:45.690
It is too dangerous out there.

17:45.863 --> 17:47.194
<i>[Sniffing]</i>

17:47.932 --> 17:50.765
Forgive me, my queen, I spoke out of turn.

17:56.340 --> 18:00.504
Yes, Your Majesty,
I will tell my people about you.

18:00.945 --> 18:05.882
<i>And may I be so bold as to ask you
to tell your subjects about...</i>

18:06.417 --> 18:07.509
Uh-oh.

18:07.952 --> 18:09.078
[Humming]

18:09.520 --> 18:13.422
PEGGY: I'm telling you, it's Dale,
with those fire ants. Get right in his...

18:13.490 --> 18:14.479
Dale!

18:16.327 --> 18:17.589
Oh, man.

18:17.661 --> 18:20.221
Dale, you went too far this time!

18:20.297 --> 18:23.460
Come back here. I'm gonna kick your ass!

18:23.534 --> 18:24.762
DALE: No!

18:24.835 --> 18:27.531
HANK: I'm gonna kick it harder
if you don't come over here!

18:27.604 --> 18:30.539
DALE: You shouldn't have fired me!
You know what I'm like!

18:30.607 --> 18:33.007
<i>I'm capable of any crazy thing!</i>

18:33.077 --> 18:36.513
But my lawn, Dale!
You don't mess with a man's lawn!

18:36.580 --> 18:38.013
I had no choice!

18:38.082 --> 18:41.210
I tried planting the ants in your driveway,
but they didn't take!

18:41.285 --> 18:44.982
They couldn't bite through cement.
They're weak! Like me!

18:45.055 --> 18:46.579
BOBBY: Dad.

18:46.657 --> 18:49.057
HANK: Not now, Bobby!
I'm in the middle of something!

18:49.126 --> 18:51.390
BOBBY: This really can't wait.

18:52.863 --> 18:54.455
Bobby, what are you doing?

18:54.531 --> 18:55.896
Take them off!

18:55.966 --> 18:58.662
DALE: Bobby, don't move a muscle!
BOBBY: What?

18:58.736 --> 19:01.967
Listen to him, Bobby. If you move,
they're all gonna sting at once.

19:02.039 --> 19:05.202
Take my hand, Bobby.
The ants'll swarm on me.

19:05.275 --> 19:06.572
What if they don't?

19:06.643 --> 19:08.474
They will.

19:08.545 --> 19:12.879
<i>They've been waiting
to get a piece of me for 15 years.</i>

19:13.217 --> 19:15.617
Come and get it, boys.

19:16.186 --> 19:17.813
[Dale groaning]

19:20.024 --> 19:21.013
Ouch.

19:23.193 --> 19:24.182
HANK: Dale?

19:25.929 --> 19:29.023
BOBBY: Mr. Gribble?
HANK: Dale, no!

19:30.934 --> 19:34.631
Oh, God. You sacrificed your life...

19:34.705 --> 19:36.832
to save my son.

19:36.907 --> 19:41.037
I guess that makes us even
for you ruining my lawn.

19:42.279 --> 19:45.009
<i>What am I saying?
Of course it makes us even.</i>

19:45.082 --> 19:46.071
[Crying]

19:46.150 --> 19:47.139
[Coughs]

19:49.653 --> 19:53.111
While I was blacked out,
was anything inserted into me?

19:53.524 --> 19:56.823
- You're alive?
- Answer the question.

19:57.461 --> 19:59.793
[Cheerful Mexican music playing]

20:05.702 --> 20:06.760
[Tape rewinding]

20:06.837 --> 20:08.737
<i>ANNOUNCER: It's on the green.</i>

20:08.806 --> 20:09.932
HANK: Beautiful.

20:10.474 --> 20:11.736
<i>ANNOUNCER: It's on the green.</i>

20:11.809 --> 20:13.674
<i>So green and soothing.</i>

20:13.744 --> 20:15.041
[Hollering]

20:15.112 --> 20:16.739
Come join the block party!

20:16.814 --> 20:20.409
How about at least one margarita
before Bill finishes them all?

20:21.051 --> 20:24.543
It's not "margarrrita," okay?

20:24.788 --> 20:26.346
It's "margarita."

20:26.457 --> 20:27.617
[Doorbell rings]

20:29.026 --> 20:31.722
Oh, Hank? Hank, come quick.

20:33.130 --> 20:34.495
Well, I'll be...

20:35.399 --> 20:36.696
Here, Hank.

20:36.834 --> 20:39.997
I've been saving this for someone special.

20:40.437 --> 20:43.031
But I guess she's never coming back.

20:43.841 --> 20:45.809
KAHN: Try and make lawn nice, neighbor.

20:45.876 --> 20:48.845
DALE: Organically grown, no chemicals.

20:49.279 --> 20:51.907
I killed all the bugs with my fingers.

20:51.982 --> 20:53.506
[Boomhauer cheering]

20:53.584 --> 20:56.610
[Muttering] This day Hank's, man,
everybody's best friend, man!

20:56.687 --> 21:01.021
Richest man in the world.
Just like the dang old Jimmy... Yo.

21:01.091 --> 21:04.026
This is a very friendly gesture.

21:04.928 --> 21:07.055
I like y'all a whole lot.

21:07.531 --> 21:10.557
If any of you weren't here,
I'd miss you some.

21:11.168 --> 21:13.762
I especially want to thank Dale Gribble.

21:14.371 --> 21:18.774
<i>Without his paranoid
and, well, hateful nature...</i>

21:18.842 --> 21:22.437
I never would've learned what kind
of beating a friendship can survive.

21:22.513 --> 21:24.378
You're my best friend, Dale.

21:24.448 --> 21:27.144
I thought I was your best friend, Hank.

21:27.885 --> 21:29.409
Yeah, well...

21:30.254 --> 21:31.243
[Chuckles]

21:31.355 --> 21:32.656
<i>[Sighs]</i>

21:38.361 --> 21:39.953
[Hank whistling]

